task.summary: Default task
Started to play around with MouseListener.
Abstracted the creation of the fretboard image. This will be beneficial when I implement the "clear all" functionality later
First attempt at drawing the fret board. I think I can do this better though and keep the Data type as a list instead of arrays.

Using a BST I am able to get the closet points, but there is still a chance that the closest point will not be the one I wanted. I am going to have to think about this but I don't think BST is going to be the solution here sadly.
We don't need the BST because we have an established grid. This solution is much simpler and accounts for when the person clicks outside of the grid.
Adding the readme.
Abstracted the code that determines which string is the closest. This will enable me to reuse it for Barre Chords
Added my own implementation of a DocumentListener.
Fixed the bug with the intersectionPoints list. It has to be cleared every time we create the image or else we'll get relics from past runs.
Added the clear button.
Adding an Icon to the program and adjusted the notes width based on the number of strings.
Renaming the IntFilter.
Added the notes "Open", "Muted", and "Regular."
Changing the layout so it is a bit clearer as to what the user is expected to do.

Moved the Fretboard options to a new dialog. Abstracted the NotesEnum so it doesn't live in the ChordDrawer class and added the "None" type which tells the user that they must select a type before selecting note placement.
Added a root note display.
Added the ability to define a barre chord. I would like to find a way to show off that the first chord has been selected.
Adding the rough beginning of an about page?
Set the AboutDisplay to use an EditPane which allows me to call an HTML file.
Changed the about menu action title and uploading the first version of the Manifest. I hope to get the JAR file created properly by the end of today.
Set up the Project Structure so I can generate the JAR file.
Updating the about page to be more descriptive.
